        "Club career": "Born in Kuopio, Tuominen has played for Lahti, Lahti Akatemia and MP.He signed for Belarusian club BATE Borisov in March 2017 on a three-year deal, for a €370,000 transfer fee.In December 2019, Tuominen signed for Swedish club Häcken, starting in the 2020 season.He was loaned out to Norwegian Eliteserien side Tromsø IL for the 2022 season.After spending six years abroad, Tuominen returned to Finland in January 2023 and signed with Veikkausliiga club KuPS on a deal for the 2023 Veikkausliiga season. He left the club at the end of the year.On 17 January 2024, he joined Polish club Bruk-Bet Termalica Nieciecza in the second-tier I liga, on an eighteen-month contract.",
